### RAG Query Service - Smoke Tests
### This file contains sample HTTP requests for testing the RAG Query Service
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension or similar tools

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@contentType = application/json

### ======================
### Health Check Tests
### ======================

### Basic Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Detailed Health Check (tests all dependencies)
GET {{baseUrl}}/health/detailed

### Service Information
GET {{baseUrl}}/info

### ======================
### RAG Query Tests
### ======================

### Basic Query - Simple question
POST {{baseUrl}}/query
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "q": "What is machine learning?"
}

### Query with Filters - Filter by category
POST {{baseUrl}}/query
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "q": "How does neural networks work?",
  "filters": {
    "category": "ingested"
  }
}

### Query with Custom Parameters - Override search parameters
POST {{baseUrl}}/query
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "q": "What are the benefits of artificial intelligence?",
  "k": 5,
  "knn": 3,
  "includeText": true
}

### Query with Multiple Filters - Complex filtering
POST {{baseUrl}}/query
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "q": "Explain deep learning algorithms",
  "filters": {
    "category": "research",
    "filename": "ai-paper.txt"
  },
  "k": 10,
  "includeText": true
}

### Query with Vector Field Override - Use different vector field
POST {{baseUrl}}/query
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "q": "What is natural language processing?",
  "vectorField": "contentVector",
  "k": 8,
  "knn": 6
}

